This paper is primarily focused on detecting stealthy attacks using anomaly detection techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes the use of neural network models and deep learning techniques for feature extraction, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of Adversarial Autoencoder (AAE) is a specific type of neural network model that is commonly used in deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the importance of system administration and security analysis, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
